answerBox.snippet: At one grade lower, in MS66, the 1977-D is worth between $10 and $15. In MS64 and MS65, while several have recently sold for up to $6, the true price for this grade is only $1. Examples between MS60 and MS63 are quite common and command a price somewhere between $1 and face value.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: Is there anything special about a 1977 dime?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet:
Generally About What the 1977 Roosevelt Dime Is Roosevelt's picture on the obverse commemorates his administration, especially the founding of the March of Dimes to fight polio. The reverse design, which was also created by John R. Sinnock, depicts a torch with an oak and olive branch on either side.
Feb 1, 2025

peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The 1894-S Barber dime is a dime produced in the United States Barber coinage. It is one of the rarest and most highly prized United States coins for collectors, along with the 1804 dollar and the 1913 Liberty Head nickel. One was sold in 2005 for $1.3 million, and another for $1.9 million in 2007.
